==Latin==
[[Category:Latin words from Greek]]
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κολοσσός]]''' (''kolossos''), a gigantic statue at the city of [[Rhodes]] recorded as standing seventy [[ell]]s high. It was one of the [[Seven Wonders of the Ancient World]].
===Noun===
'''colossus''' (''genitive'' '''[[colossi]]'''); {{m}}, ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin second declension|second declension]]''

#a '''colossus''', especially a gigantic [[statue]]

